main event: On November 5, 1957, a small oblong object, red & green in color, was observed traveling very fast in a straight path for 2 minutes by a civilian at the Green Bay Observatory in Wisconsin.
interesting points: The object was described as small, oblong, and displaying red and green colors.
It was observed to be flying very fast in a straight path for 2 minutes.
The report does not provide sufficient data to draw a conclusion about the object.
The observer, David Nickols, was a civilian at the Green Bay Observatory.
The weather and wind conditions at the time of the sighting were clear and unlimited.
sighted object: Small oblong object, red & green, flying very fast
